# Android

## Overview
The SDK build system has several configurations:
- Android Archive Libary
- This documentation

## Pre-requisites
- Android Studio version :3.0
- Gradle plugin version  :3.0.1
- Gradle wrapper version :4.1
- NDK version :15.1.4119039
- Android SDK Plugins: Android NDK, cmake, LLDB

## Building
1.	Open the project in build/android/Gen3SDK in Android Studio for automatic setup and do gradle sync if needed.
2.	Then execute gen3_sdk/build/android/Gen3SDK/build_gen3sdk.bat(to run this batch file, user need to add JDK and Gradlew in environment path. Refer gen3_sdk/build/android/Gen3SDK/MustReadMeForAndroid.txt)
3.	Android Archive Library will be built in gen3_sdk /bin/android/libs/gen3sdk-release.aar

## Output
### Android Archive Library
`gen3_sdk/bin/android/libs/gen3sdk-release.aar`

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# iOS

## Overview
The SDK build system has several configurations:
- Framework
- This documentation

## Pre-requisites
- Minimum iOS Version Required : iOS 8.0
- Xcode Minimum Tool Version : 8.0

## Building
1. Open the 'Gen3SDK.xcodeproj' through Xcode IDE.

2. Connect any iOS devices to the mac.

3. Choose target as the selected iOS device and Run the project.

4. Now again choose the target as any simulator device and Run the project.

5. Finally GEN3SDK.framework will be generated in the path bin/ios

Note : Inorder to build universal framework we need to run the project both in simulator and real time device

## Output
### ios Framework
`gen3_sdk/bin/ios/GEN3SDK.framework`

